lexicon: {'brief': 'an abominable thing, an accursed thing', 'long': 'an abominable thing, an accursed thing.'}
{'brief': 'I abhor, detest', 'long': 'I abhor, detest, loathe.'}
{'brief': 'adoption', 'long': 'adoption, as a son into the divine family.'}

{'brief': 'I commit adultery', 'long': 'I commit adultery (of a man with a married woman, but also of a married man).'}
{'brief': 'adultery', 'long': 'adultery.'}

{'brief': 'I commit adultery', 'long': 'I commit adultery, not only of a married woman but of a married man.'}
{'brief': 'ruler of the universe', 'long': 'ruler of all, ruler of the universe, the almighty.'}
{'brief': 'an altar', 'long': 'an altar, platform; a slightly-elevated spot.'}
{'brief': 'an altar', 'long': 'an altar (for sacrifice).'}
{'brief': 'verily, truly, amen, so let it be', 'long': 'verily, truly, amen; at the end of sentences may be paraphrased by: So let it be.'}
{'brief': 'an angel, messenger', 'long': 'a messenger, generally a (supernatural) messenger from God, an angel, conveying news or behests from God to men.'}
{'brief': 'a ruler of angels, a superior angel, an archangel', 'long': 'a ruler of angels, a superior angel, an archangel.'}
{'brief': 'like the angels', 'long': 'equal to or like the angels.'}
{'brief': 'I anoint', 'long': 'I anoint.'}
{'brief': 'I anoint', 'long': 'I anoint, consecrate by anointing.'}
{'brief': 'an anointing', 'long': 'an anointing.'}
{'brief': 'I anoint', 'long': 'I anoint: festivally, in homage, medicinally, or in anointing the dead.'}
{'brief': 'I rub in, anoint', 'long': 'I rub in, anoint.'}
{'brief': 'I spread on, anoint', 'long': 'I spread on, anoint.'}

{'brief': 'an apostle, a messenger, an envoy, a delegate', 'long': 'a messenger, envoy, delegate, one commissioned by another to represent him in some way, especially a man sent out by Jesus Christ Himself to preach the Gospel; an apostle.'}
{'brief': 'I appoint, make', 'long': '(a) I appoint, make (of a covenant), (b) I make (a will).'}
{'brief': 'I put, place', 'long': 'I put, place, lay, set, fix, establish.'}
{'brief': 'I set, establish, appoint, conduct', 'long': 'I set down, bring down to a place; I set in order, appoint, make, constitute.'}
{'brief': 'I lie, recline, am laid', 'long': 'I lie, recline, am placed, am laid, set, specially appointed, destined.'}
{'brief': 'I do, make', 'long': '(a) I make, manufacture, construct, (b) I do, act, cause.'}
{'brief': 'I appoint, choose, elect', 'long': 'I appoint, choose, elect, take into hand.'}
{'brief': 'appointed before', 'long': 'appointed before; a previously-appointed time.'}
{'brief': 'I instruct, command, appoint', 'long': '(a) I instruct, command, (b) I appoint, assign.'}
{'brief': 'I assign, arrange', 'long': '(a) I assign, arrange, (b) I determine; mid: I appoint.'}
{'brief': 'I show forth, show clearly, proclaim, appoint', 'long': "I show forth, show clearly; hence: I proclaim (a person's appointment to an office), appoint."}
{'brief': 'I define, determine, appoint, decree', 'long': 'I separate, mark off by boundaries; I determine, appoint, designate.'}
{'brief': 'an ark', 'long': '(properly: a wooden box, hence) the Ark, in which Noah sailed; the Ark of the Covenant.'}

{'brief': 'a sin offering, covering', 'long': '(a) a sin offering, by which the wrath of the deity shall be appeased; a means of propitiation, (b) the covering of the ark, which was sprinkled with the atoning blood on the Day of Atonement.'}
{'brief': 'I domineer over', 'long': 'I domineer, govern, have mastery over.'}
{'brief': 'a ruler, potentate', 'long': '(lit: a man who rules by force), a ruler, potentate; also: courtier, member of the court.'}
{'brief': 'I have power over', 'long': 'I have (exercise) power (authority) over.'}
{'brief': 'lordship, domination, dignity', 'long': '(a) abstr: lordship, (b) concr: divine or angelic lordship, domination, dignity, usually with reference to a celestial hierarchy.'}

{'brief': 'power, authority, weight', 'long': '(a) power, authority, weight, especially: moral authority, influence, (b) in a quasi-personal sense, derived from later Judaism, of a spiritual power, and hence of an earthly power.'}
{'brief': 'I exercise authority', 'long': 'I exercise (wield) power (authority), pass: I am ruled, am held under authority.'}
{'brief': 'instruction, command, order, authority', 'long': 'instruction, command, order, authority.'}
{'brief': 'superiority, excellence', 'long': 'superiority, excellence, preeminence, authority.'}
{'brief': 'the baptizer, the Baptist', 'long': 'the baptizer, the Baptist, epithet used only of John, the son of Zechariah and Elizabeth, forerunner of Jesus.'}
{'brief': 'I dip, submerge, baptize', 'long': 'lit: I dip, submerge, but specifically of ceremonial dipping; I baptize.'}
{'brief': 'the rite or ceremony of baptism', 'long': 'the rite or ceremony of baptism.'}
{'brief': 'dipping, washing', 'long': 'dipping, washing (of a ceremonial character).'}
{'brief': 'faith, belief, trust', 'long': 'faith, belief, trust, confidence; fidelity, faithfulness.'}
{'brief': 'I believe, have faith in', 'long': 'I believe, have faith in, trust in; pass: I am entrusted with.'}
{'brief': 'trustworthy, faithful, believing', 'long': 'trustworthy, faithful, believing.'}
{'brief': 'unbelieving, incredulous, unchristian, unbeliever', 'long': 'unbelieving, incredulous, unchristian; sometimes subst: unbeliever.'}
{'brief': 'unbelief, unfaithfulness, distrust', 'long': 'unbelief, unfaithfulness, distrust.'}

{'brief': 'loved, beloved', 'long': 'loved, beloved, with two special applications: the Beloved, a title of the Messiah (Christ), as beloved beyond all others by the God who sent Him; of Christians, as beloved by God, Christ, and one another.'}

{'brief': 'the birthright', 'long': 'the birthright, the rights of the first-born.'}
{'brief': 'blameless', 'long': 'blameless, free from fault or defect.'}
{'brief': 'blamelessly', 'long': 'blamelessly.'}
{'brief': 'blameless', 'long': 'blameless, without blemish, unblemished, faultless.'}
{'brief': 'irreproachable, blameless', 'long': 'irreproachable, blameless.'}
{'brief': 'irreproachable', 'long': 'irreproachable, never caught doing wrong.'}
{'brief': 'not offending, not causing offence, blameless', 'long': '(free from hurt or harm, hence) not offending, not causing offence, blameless.'}
{'brief': 'slanderous', 'long': 'slanderous; subst: a blasphemer.'}
{'brief': 'I speak evil against, blaspheme', 'long': 'I speak evil against, blaspheme, use abusive or scurrilous language about (God or men).'}
{'brief': 'abusive or scurrilous language, blasphemy', 'long': 'abusive or scurrilous language, blasphemy.'}
{'brief': 'worthy of praise, blessed', 'long': '(used only of God), blessed (as entitled to receive blessing from man), worthy of praise.'}

{'brief': 'adulation, praise, blessing', 'long': 'adulation, praise, blessing, gift.'}
{'brief': 'I make straight, direct', 'long': '(a) I make straight, (b) met: I put in the right way, direct.'}

{'brief': 'I bless', 'long': 'I bless (of God).'}
{'brief': 'blood', 'long': 'blood (especially as shed).'}
{'brief': "with one's own hand", 'long': "with one's own hand."}

{'brief': 'vainglorious', 'long': 'vainglorious, boastful.'}

{'brief': 'a boaster', 'long': "a boaster, one who gives one's self airs in a loud and flaunting way."}
{'brief': 'I dwell in, among', 'long': 'I dwell in, among.'}
